<p>Omaha's cold climate demands robust heating systems capable of handling winter temperatures that regularly drop below freezing. For optimal year-round comfort and efficiency, homeowners should consider high-efficiency furnaces with AFUE ratings of 90% or higher, paired with central air conditioning systems rated at minimum 14 SEER for cooling efficiency. Heat pumps can be effective in Omaha, but cold-climate models with backup heating are essential for reliable operation during harsh winter conditions.</p>

